Girl Scouts Digital Media Course
October 29, 2010 | Session 3
Fun with photos (part 2)
• Learn how to use layer blending modes for fun effects
goals for the day:
• Become familiar with the paint bucket, gradient, & blur tools
• Combine layer blending modes and masking for digital face painting!
KEY TERMS:
layer blending mode - one of the many ways you can blend two images together.
gradient - a fade from one color to another. Gradients can have multiple colors
that blend into one another (for example, the gradient below has eight.)
opacity - how transparent / see-through vs. how opaque an image is.
QUESTION OF THE DAY:
If a Hollywood makeup artist offered to do your look for Halloween, what face
paint, makeup, and/or hair dye would you ask for?
#1: THREE WAYS TO BLEND
There are three main ways to use layer blending modes with an images. Nicki
is going to help us see what they are and how they look!
• Learn how to tune layer opacity, making layers partially transparent

PAGE 4
ACTIVITY
BLEND A PHOTO WITH
ANOTHER PHOTO!
First, open up your photo in Gimp, then drag your second
photo into the image so both photos are separate layers.
Next, select a layer blending mode for the photo on top. Experiment.
Depending on the photos you've chosen, you may want to flip or move the
photos to strengthen your composition.
Try changing the order of the photos. Depending on which photo is on the top
and which photo is o the bottom, the final effect may look different. You may
do these by selecting a layer to move (simply
click on it), then click either the layer up button
or the layer down button.

Feel free to blend as many photos together as
you'd like. You can stick with to or work with
10. It's up to you. You can also use fill or pattern
layers inbetween as well.
REVIEW QUESTIONS
Can you name three layer blending modes? How does each make your image
look when you use it?
For really cool face-paint effects, try to
find a photo of an animal or pattern to face
paint onto your face. For example, find a photo
of fish scales or a zebra's fur. Then, use a layer
mask to 'paint' the animal's pattern onto your
face.
How do you create a gradient?
How would you dye your hair pink using the Gimp, step-by-step?
What tool would you use to make a layer transparet?
EXTRA CREDIT
Find a photo of your favorite celebrity, and turn them into a zombie for Halloween!
